@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### GET / — list endpoints
GET {{baseUrl}}/

###

### POST /upload/single — single file in memory
# Replace the file path with a real file on your system
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/single
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="hello.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

Hello, Darto!
------FormBoundary--

###

### POST /upload/multiple — multiple files in memory
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/multiple
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="a.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

File A content
------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="files"; filename="b.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

File B content
------FormBoundary--

###

### POST /upload/disk — streamed to disk (uploads/ directory)
POST {{baseUrl}}/upload/disk
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=----FormBoundary

------FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="file"; filename="large.txt"
Content-Type: text/plain

This file will be saved to disk instead of memory.
------FormBoundary--
